desc: A Japanese general of the Genpei War near the end of the Heian era and start of the Kamakura era. His bold ingenuity and ruthless skill with a blade are still praised in Japan today.

name: Alice
desc: A mysterious blond girl. She is quite powerful, despite her looks. Some say she is the ghost of a girl who died a sad death. Others say she is a spirit born from someone's imagination.

name: Pazuzu
desc: The Babylonian lord of wind and scorching sands. He has the body of a man, a lion's head, the claws and wings of an eagle, and has a deadly poison. The diseases he spreads can only be cured with magic.

name: Mokoi
desc: Evil spirits of Murngin lore believed to be reborn shadows. They kidnap and eat children, and strike down any sorcerer who uses black magic.

name: Dominion
desc: The fourth of the nine orders of angels. Their duty is to oversee the other angels. Their actions are the manifestation of God's will.

name: Isis
desc: Osiris's wife as well as his younger sister. Upon the death of her husband, she revived him with her incredible magic power. Isis is seen at many gravesites as the guardian goddess of the dead.

name: Clotho
desc: The youngest of the three Moirae Sisters of Greek legend. She spins the threads of life with her spindle.

name: Sandalphon
desc: Metatron's twin brother in Judeo-Christian lore, he is the master of heavenly songs. It is said that a human would take 500 years to walk the length of his body.

name: Thor
desc: The Norse thunder god and son of Odin, Thor owns the power-enhancing belt Megingjard and wields Mjolnir, a hammer that causes lightning to strike and returns to its owner if thrown.

name: Anubis
desc: The jackal-headed god of the dead and embalming from Egyptian myth. He weighs the hearts of the dead to determine their final destination.

name: Parvati
desc: A beautiful Hindu goddess of love and one of Shiva's wives. Always by his side, she played a role in opening his third eye. She can turn into Durga or Kali when angered.

name: Jack-o'-Lantern
desc: A drunkard who tricked the Devil out of taking him to Hell. When refused entry to Heaven, he was forced to wander the earth with only an ember as a light.

desc: One of the Ssu-Ling, celestial creatures of Chinese myth. It represents the direction north, the season of winter, and the element of water. Known to be a great warrior, it supports the Earth from below.
strategy:
1. At the start of battle, Genbu will gain <color=#FF423F>Black Tortoiseshell</color> stacks equal to its <color=#FF423F>Down Points</color>, and its Defense and damage reduction will increase with each stack.
2. When Genbu is hit by an attack other than its weakness or a Physical critical, it will gain 1 <color=#FF423F>Down Point</color> and <color=#FF423F>Black Tortoiseshell</color> stack each. When hit by its weakness or a Physical critical attack, it will lose 1 <color=#FF423F>Black Tortoiseshell</color> stack.
3. When Genbu is at 8 Black Tortoiseshell stacks on its action, it will activate <color=#FF423F>Genbu's Rage</color>, dealing heavy Ice damage to all Phantom Thieves.
4. The effect of <color=#FF423F>Black Tortoiseshell</color> also applies to other Shadows.

3. If Archangel's <color=#FF423F>shield</color> is broken, all Phantom Thieves will recover from <color=#FF423F>Dizziness</color>.

2. The Shadow has 2 stances, <color=#FF423F>Attack Position</color> and <color=#FF423F>Defense Position</color>.
<color=#FF423F>Attack Position</color> increases Attack by 10% each turn, and resets when the stance is changed.
<color=#FF423F>Defense Position</color> increases Defense by 10% each turn, and resets when the stance is changed.
3. At the start of battle, Archangel selects 1 Phantom Thief, and changes stances each time it is attacked by that Thief. The selected Thief cannot become <color=#FF423F>Dizzy</color>.
4. When in Attack Position, Archangel will use Lunge against all Phantom Thieves. When in Defense Position, Archangel will cause attackers to become <color=#FF423F>Dizzy</color>.

2. On Eligor's turn, it summons 1 Berith and activates <color=#FF423F>Royal Aid</color>.
<color=#FF423F>Royal Aid</color> is granted to 1 Berith, heals 50% of its max HP, negates 50% of damage taken for 1 turn, and inflicts <color=#FF423F>Taunt</color> on all Phantom Thieves.
3. If a Berith is defeated, Eligor loses a certain amount of HP.
4. If the number of Beriths increases, Eligor activates <color=#FF423F>Royal Conquest</color>, dealing heavy Physical damage to all Phantom Thieves.

name: Yaksini
desc: A female demon in Hindu lore. Though originally a Dravidian fertility goddess, the spread of Hinduism changed perception of her to a demonic figure. Usually depicted as a nude, voluptuous female.
strategy:
1. Every 2 turns, Yaksini will activate True Wage War.
True Wage War has a high chance to <color=#FF423F>Enrage</color> all Phantom Thieves.
<color=#FF423F>Rage</color> causes the target to <color=#FF423F>use normal attacks uncontrollably</color>. Attack is greatly increased, and Defense is greatly decreased.
2. When Yaksini is attacked, it gains 1 Yaksha stack, increasing its Attack for each stack.

desc: An exceptionally powerful shikigami. Only the most elite onmyoji are able to summon and bind it to paper. It can ward off disaster or cure illness, but its ordinary temperament is quite vicious.

desc: A type of tengu. Their spiritual power is weaker than other tengu, so they are much smaller. They are said to be the reincarnations of long-lived wolves.

name: Nue
desc: A creature of Japanese lore with a monkey's head, tiger's legs, and snake's tail. The Tale of Heike says it hid behind a dark cloud each night to attack the Emperor.
strategy:
When Nue acts, Nue and other Shadows will gain one of the following random buffs for 1 turn:
<color=#72C5FF>Monkey Mask</color>: At the end of turn, restore a set amount of HP. When inflicted with an elemental ailment, cure it.
<color=#72C5FF>Tanuki Form</color>: Gain an 80% chance to dodge. When inflicted with a spiritual ailment, cure it.
<color=#72C5FF>Tiger Claws</color>: Greatly increase damage.
<color=#72C5FF>Snake Tail</color>: Inflict Poison when dealing damage.

name: Orobas
desc: One of the 72 demons of the Goetia. Known as the Prince of Hell, he appears as a horse and answers questions of the past, present, and future. He is faithful to his conjurer.

name: Jack Frost
desc: A winter fairy of European descent. He leaves ice patterns on windows and nips people's noses. Though normally an innocent creature, he will freeze his victims to death if provoked.

name: Angel
desc: The ninth of the nine orders of angels. They are closest in nature to humans. They watch over individuals and warn those who stray from the path.

name: Nue
desc: A creature of Japanese lore with a monkey's head, tiger's legs, and snake's tail. The Tale of Heike says it hid behind a dark cloud each night to attack the Emperor.

<color=#72C5FF>Monkey Mask</color>: At the end of turn, restore a set amount of HP. When inflicted with an elemental ailment, cure it.

<color=#72C5FF>Tiger Claws</color>: Greatly increase damage.
<color=#72C5FF>Snake Tail</color>: Inflict Poison when dealing damage.
<color=#72C5FF>Nue's Power</color>: Greatly increase Attack and Defense.

name: Oni
desc: An evil monster from Japanese lore known for its hideous visage and brute strength. They loot and plunder villages, massacring the townspeople with their iron clubs. They have horns on their heads, red skin, long claws, and razor-sharp teeth.
strategy:
1. Oni always has <color=#72C5FF>Absolute Counter</color>. Whenever it takes damage, it will counterattack, dealing single-target Physical damage to the attacker.
2. Whenever Oni counterattacks, a count is added, and when the count reaches 4, it activates Hyakki Yagyo, dealing heavy damage to all Phantom Thieves.
3. On each of Oni's turns, 1 Phantom Thief gains <color=#72C5FF>Oni Slayer</color>. A Phantom Thief in this state will not activate Oni's Absolute Counter for 1 turn.
4. When Obariyon is defeated, all Phantom Thieves gain <color=#72C5FF>Oni Slayer</color> for 1 turn.

strategy:

desc: An exceptionally powerful shikigami. Only the most elite onmyoji are able to summon and bind it to paper. It can ward off disaster or cure illness, but its ordinary temperament is quite vicious.

3. If Shiki-Ouji has Woe at the start of its turn, it changes to Disaster. When it has 3 Disaster stacks, it automatically activates Karma, dealing heavy damage to all Phantom Thieves.

name: Jikokuten
desc: Also known as Dhritarashtra, he is the protector of the East, and is one of the four Heavenly Kings of Buddhist origin. He helps maintain the security of the nation.
strategy:
1. Jikokuten starts the battle with 10 Down Points. Every 2 turns, it activates Blade of Sanctuary, granting itself 10 Down Points, and granting 1 Down Point to all Shadows. When Jikokuten's Down Points reach 36, it transforms into <color=#FF423F>Asura</color>, greatly enhancing its abilities.
2. Jikokuten constantly summons various Shadows. When a Shadow is defeated, Jikokuten's Down Points are reduced by 3.
3. Victory can be achieved by reducing Jikokuten's Down Points to 0, or by defeating all foes.

name: Kikuri-Hime
desc: The goddess of life in Shinto myth. She once mediated between Izanagi and Izanami during their confrontation in Yomi, the land of the dead.
strategy:
Each turn, Kikuri-Hime will use a random Arbiter's Power on the Phantom Thieves, forbidding them from taking certain actions.
If the Phantom Thieves defy the arbitration, they receive 1 Seal of Mortality, and if they receive 2 seals, they are KO'd.
Arbitration - Survival: If Healing and Defense skills or Highlights are used, receive 1 Seal of Mortality.
Arbitration - Attack: If Attack skills or Highlights are used, receive 1 Seal of Mortality.
Arbitration - Support: If Buff and Debuff skills or Highlights are used, receive 1 Seal of Mortality.
If all Phantom Thieves obey the arbitration, Kikuri-Hime will grant all Phantom Thieves a damage increase effect.

name: Anubis
desc: The jackal-headed god of the dead and embalming from Egyptian myth. He weighs the hearts of the dead to determine their final destination.
strategy:
Anubis has no weaknesses or resistances. Angel and Succubus have different weaknesses and resistances than normal.
1. When Angel takes damage, Anubis gains 1 Judgment of Evil stack.
2. When Succubus takes damage, Anubis gains 1 Judgment of Good stack.
3. Judgment of Good and Judgment of Evil cancel each other out.
4. When either Judgment of Good or Judgment of Evil reach 5 stacks, Anubis will use Advent of Judgment, dealing heavy damage to all Phantom Thieves.

name: Angel
desc: The ninth of the nine orders of angels. They are closest in nature to humans. They watch over individuals and warn those who stray from the path.

name: Succubus
desc: A female demon of European lore in medieval times. They visit sleeping men and have sexual intercourse with them. The victims don't wake up but may dream of the encounter.

name: Anubis
desc: The jackal-headed god of the dead and embalming from Egyptian myth. He weighs the hearts of the dead to determine their final destination.
strategy:
1. After receiving a debuff, Anubis gains 1 Judgment of Evil stack.
2. After receiving a buff, Anubis gains 1 Judgment of Good stack.
3. Judgment of Good and Judgment of Evil cancel each other out.
4. When either Judgment of Good or Judgment of Evil reach 5 stacks, Anubis will use Advent of Judgment, dealing heavy damage to all Phantom Thieves.
5. At the start of each turn, Anubis will summon 1 Saki Mitama.

name: Saki Mitama
desc: One of the four aspects of Shinto thought, it brings great bounty from the hunt. It is said to aid in love, profit, and growth, and can create new paths.

name: Anubis
desc: The jackal-headed god of the dead and embalming from Egyptian myth. He weighs the hearts of the dead to determine their final destination.
strategy:
Anubis has no weaknesses or resistances.
1. When the Phantom Thieves use a debuff skill or attack skill, Anubis gains 1 Judgment of Evil.
2. When the Phantom Thieves use a buff skill or a healing skill, Anubis gains 1 Judgment of Good.
3.Judgment of Good and Judgment of Evil cancel each other out.
4. When either Judgment of Good or Judgment of Evil reach 5 stacks, Anubis will use Advent of Judgment, dealing heavy damage to all Phantom Thieves.

name: Hariti
desc: Also known as Kishimojin, she once ate children, but stopped after Buddha changed her ways. She now eats pomegranates and is a goddess of parenting.
strategy:
Hariti has no weaknesses or resistances.
1. Hariti has extremely high damage reduction, making it difficult to deal damage with direct attacks.
2. When Hariti's turn ends, it spends its own HP to fully heal all other Shadows, losing HP equal to the amount healed.
3. At the start of Hariti's turn, it summons 1 Agathion. Hariti's damage increases by 15% for each Agathion on the field.

name: Agathion
desc: A general term for familiars used by Judeo-Christian magicians, they are usually sealed away in bottles, rings, or talismans. They torment the target selected by the conjuror.

name: Hariti
desc: Also known as Kishimojin, she once ate children, but stopped after Buddha changed her ways. She now eats pomegranates and is a goddess of parenting.
strategy:
Hariti has no weaknesses or resistances.
1. Hariti has extremely high damage reduction, making it difficult to deal damage with direct attacks.
2. When Hariti's turn ends, it spends its own HP to fully heal all other Shadows, losing HP equal to the amount healed.
3. When Jack-o'-Lantern is defeated, Hariti immediately deals heavy damage to all Phantom Thieves.
4. At the start of Hariti's turn, it summons up to 4 Jack-o'-Lanterns.

name: Jack-o'-Lantern
desc: A drunkard who tricked the Devil out of taking him to Hell. When refused entry to Heaven, he was forced to wander the earth with only an ember as a light.

name: Hariti
desc: Also known as Kishimojin, she once ate children, but stopped after Buddha changed her ways. She now eats pomegranates and is a goddess of parenting.
strategy:
Hariti, Jack Frost, and Black Frost have no weaknesses or resistances.
1. Hariti has extremely high damage reduction, making it difficult to deal damage with direct attacks.
2. When Hariti's turn ends, it spends its own HP to fully heal all other Shadows, losing HP equal to the amount healed.
3. Each turn, Hariti summons 1 Jack Frost, and grants Mother's Love to a random Jack Frost.
4. A Jack Frost with Mother's Love will grow into Black Frost after 2 turns, gaining higher Attack and Defense, but also becoming unable to receive healing effects.

name: Jack Frost
desc: A winter fairy of European descent. He leaves ice patterns on windows and nips people's noses. Though normally an innocent creature, he will freeze his victims to death if provoked.

name: Black Frost
desc: A Jack Frost that yearned for evil. This powerful demon is born when a cute Jack Frost remembers its demonic nature.

name: Kumbhanda
desc: A Buddhist demon said to drain human life energy. He has dark skin, stands three meters tall, and sometimes changes his shape to a gourd. Known to have once served Rudra, the god of storms.
strategy:
1. Every turn, Kumbhanda will attack Phantom Thieves who have a Grudge stack. If no Phantom Thieves have a Grudge, it will attack all Phantom Thieves.
2. Whenever Kumbhanda attacks, it decreases the target's max HP by 20%, and increases the max HP of the Agathion with the lowest HP by 20%.

name: Agathion
desc: A general term for familiars used by Judeo-Christian magicians, they are usually sealed away in bottles, rings, or talismans. They torment the target selected by the conjuror.
strategy:
1. When Agathion is hit by an attack, the attacker is inflicted with 1 Grudge stack for 1 turn.
2. If an Agathion's HP is less than 40% at the start of its turn, it transforms into Kumbhanda. If it is defeated, it restores the HP of all Shadows by 40%.

name: Kumbhanda
desc: A Buddhist demon said to drain human life energy. He has dark skin, stands three meters tall, and sometimes changes his shape to a gourd. Known to have once served Rudra, the god of storms.
strategy:
1. Every turn, Kumbhanda will attack Phantom Thieves who have a Grudge stack. If no Phantom Thieves have a Grudge, it will attack all Phantom Thieves.
2. Whenever Kumbhanda attacks, it reduces the target's SP by 20 and restores 10 SP to a random Agathion.

name: Girimehkala
desc: A giant elephant monster of Sri Lankan myth, it is typically portrayed as being ridden by the Evil One, Mara. Whoever looks into its evil eye is said to be met with misfortune.
strategy:
1. Each turn, Girimehkala inflicts <color=#FF423F>Mark of Calamity</color> on 2 Phantom Thieves for 2 turns.
2. When a Phantom Thief or Shadow with Mark of Calamity deals damage with a skill, <color=#FF423F>Calamity's Descent</color> is activated 1 time. Calamity's Descent: Deals multi-target damage based on the user's Attack and transfers a Mark of Calamity onto the main target.
3. All Shadows' final damage (excluding that of Calamity's Descent) is decreased by 60%.
4. After taking damage from Calamity's Descent, damage taken is greatly increased. This effect lasts for 1 turn.

desc: A male demon of European lore in medieval times. They visit sleeping women and have sexual intercourse with them. The resulting children become witches or wizards.

desc: A female demon of European lore in medieval times. They visit sleeping men and have sexual intercourse with them. The victims don't wake up but may dream of the encounter.

name: Belphegor
desc: Demonic governor of the deadly sin of sloth. He also excels at invention and discovery. May be derived from Ba'al Pe'or, Syrian god of abundant crops.
strategy:
Weaknesses and resistances are different than normal.
1. Belphegor is always inflicted with <color=#FF423F>Sleep</color>. After being attacked, it will wake up, and can take 1 action before going back to sleep.
2. Each time Belphegor acts, it gains 1 <color=#FF423F>Enraged</color> stack, and its damage increases by 40% with each stack.

name: Sandman
desc: A fairy in German folklore who carries a bag of magical sand, which puts humans to sleep when thrown into their eyes. If the victim resists, the Sandman will sit on their eyelids.
strategy: When Sandman is defeated, Belphegor will go to Sleep.

name: Valkyrie
desc: "Choosers of the slain" in Norse lore. Armed with shining armor and swords, they look for brave warriors to take to Valhalla, so that they may fight in Ragnarok.
strategy:
Weaknesses and resistances are different than normal.
1. When 3 Shadows have been defeated, the Shadows will leave and Valkyrie will appear.
2. Valkyrie will receive buffs based on the defeated Shadows.
Setanta's Will: At the end of the turn, restores 20% of HP. Stacks up to 3 times.

name: Seiryu
desc: The noblest of the Ssu-Ling creatures of Chinese myth. It represents the direction east, the season of spring, and the element of wood. It dwells in a palace at the bottom of the ocean.
strategy:
1. Seiryu alternates between inflicting weaknesses to Psychokinesis and Nuclear. These effects last for 2 turns.
2. When a Phantom Thief is knocked down, Seiryu gains 1 <color=#FF423F>Azure Storm</color> stack.
Azure Storm: Damage increases by 30%.When Azure Storm reaches 6 stacks, Seiryu deals heavy damage to all Phantom Thieves.
3. Every 2 turns, Seiryu summons 1 Phoenix and 1 Leanan Sidhe. Phoenix uses Nuclear skills, and Leanan Sidhe uses Psychokinesis skills.

name: Phoenix
desc: The legendary bird of Chinese myth, said to appear only in times of peace. It is the ruler of all birds. When it dies, birds across the land chirp with sadness.

name: Leanan Sidhe
desc: A beautiful fairy of Irish lore that yearns for the love of a human man. She drains the life of her lovers in return for granting them artistic inspiration.

name: Seiryu
desc: The noblest of the Ssu-Ling creatures of Chinese myth. It represents the direction east, the season of spring, and the element of wood. It dwells in a palace at the bottom of the ocean.
strategy:
1. Seiryu alternates between inflicting weaknesses to Wind and Ice. These effects last for 2 turns.
2. When a Phantom Thief is knocked down, Seiryu gains 1 <color=#FF423F>Azure Storm</color> stack.
Azure Storm: Damage increases by 30%.When Azure Storm reaches 6 stacks, Seiryu deals heavy damage to all Phantom Thieves.
3. At the start of the turn, if there are no Sudama or Kodama on the field, 1 Sudama or Kodama will be summoned.

name: Anzu
desc: An evil deity of Mesopotamian folklore with an eagle's body and lion's head. While the god Enlil purified himself, Anzu stole the Tablets of Destiny from him.

name: Sudama
desc: A spirit of rivers and mountains in Japanese lore, it dwells in ancient trees and ageless rocks. They are not evil, and will often appear as humans or supernatural wonders to warn people.
strategy: When defeated, all Phantom Thieves gain Wind Wall and change Wind affinity to Resist for 1 turn.

name: Kodama
desc: Japanese plant spirits born from trees that have lived for a hundred years. Cutting down one of these trees is said to cause misfortune.
strategy: When defeated, all Phantom Thieves gain Ice Wall and change Ice affinity to Resist for 1 turn.

name: Seiryu
desc: The noblest of the Ssu-Ling creatures of Chinese myth. It represents the direction east, the season of spring, and the element of wood. It dwells in a palace at the bottom of the ocean.
strategy:
1. Each turn, Seiryu will record the attributes of damage it takes, and on the next turn inflicts a weakness to that attribute to a Shadow.
2. When a Phantom Thief is knocked down, Seiryu gains 1 <color=#FF423F>Azure Storm</color> stack.
Azure Storm: Damage increases by 30%. When Azure Storm reaches 6 stacks, Seiryu deals heavy damage to all Phantom Thieves.

name: Saki Mitama
desc: One of the four aspects of Shinto thought, it brings great bounty from the hunt. It is said to aid in love, profit, and growth, and can create new paths.
strategy: Alternates between using Electric and Bless attacks.

name: Nigi Mitama
desc: One of the four aspects of Shinto thought, it works gently to help maintain a calm mind. It is said to aid in one's relations and sociability, and can lead one in a positive direction.
strategy: Alternates between using Wind and Curse attacks.

name: Kushi Mitama
desc: One of the four aspects of Shinto thought, it uses its power to bring blessings related to healing illnesses and staying healthy. It is said to have supernatural powers and cause mysterious events.
strategy: Alternates between using Ice and Nuclear attacks.

name: Ara Mitama
desc: One of the four aspects of Shinto thought, it has the power to grant ferocity. It is said to aid in one's bravery, growth, and endeavors, though it can lead in a negative direction.
strategy: Alternates between using Fire and Psychokinesis attacks.

name: Raja Naga
desc: The king of the Naga, a half-man, half-snake tribe in Hindu lore. The dragon kings Nanda and Takshaka of Buddhist myth fall into this royal category.
strategy:
Weaknesses and resistances are different than normal.
1. Raja Naga alternates between Royal Blessing and Royal Punishment.
2. Royal Blessing: Greatly strengthens 1 Shadow, and when that Shadow attacks, it can inflict Brainwash on 1 Phantom Thief.
3. Royal Punishment: Locks on to a Phantom Thief, and deals heavy damage on the next turn. If Shadows take damage from 4 different attribute types, the lock on will be lost.

name: Naga
desc: Half-snake, half-human divine beings in Hindu lore, worshipped as bringers of rain. They live in the bottoms of lakes and seas, singing and dancing when they are not fighting.

name: Naga
desc: Half-snake, half-human divine beings in Hindu lore, worshipped as bringers of rain. They live in the bottoms of lakes and seas, singing and dancing when they are not fighting.

name: Raja Naga
desc: The king of the Naga, a half-man, half-snake tribe in Hindu lore. The dragon kings Nanda and Takshaka of Buddhist myth fall into this royal category.
strategy:
Weaknesses and resistances are different than normal.
1. Raja Naga alternates between Royal Blessing and Royal Punishment.
2. Royal Blessing: Greatly strengthens 1 ally Shadow, and when that Shadow attacks, increases all Shadows' ailment resistance.
3. Royal Punishment: Locks on to the Phantom Thief with the highest Attack, and deals heavy damage on the next turn. If Shadows are inflicted with a total of 15 debuffs, the lock on will be removed.

name: Naga
desc: Half-snake, half-human divine beings in Hindu lore, worshipped as bringers of rain. They live in the bottoms of lakes and seas, singing and dancing when they are not fighting.

name: Byakko
desc: One of the Ssu-Ling, celestial creatures of Chinese myth. It represents the direction west, the season of autumn, and the element of metal. He is believed to be the king of all beasts.
strategy:
1. Byakko will use <color=#72C5FF>Byakko's Claw</color> and <color=#72C5FF>Byakko's Fang</color>.
2. Byakko's Claw: Deals damage to 1 target and inflicts <color=#72C5FF>Deep Wounds</color>. This effect deals damage over time, and can be removed by receiving healing 3 times.
3. Byakko's Fang: Deals damage to all targets and inflicts <color=#72C5FF>Bite Marks</color>. This effect increases damage taken, and can be removed by dealing damage 3 times.
4. At the start of each turn, if both Deep Wounds and Bite Marks have been inflicted, Byakko will activate <color=#72C5FF>Prey</color>, dealing heavy damage and inflicting <color=#72C5FF>Despair</color> on the target.
5. Every two turns, 1 Leanan Sidhe will be summoned.

name: Leanan Sidhe
desc: A beautiful fairy of Irish lore that yearns for the love of a human man. She drains the life of her lovers in return for granting them artistic inspiration.
strategy: 2 turns after being summoned, inflicts Recovery Block on all Phantom Thieves. Lasts for 2 turns.

name: Byakko
desc: One of the Ssu-Ling, celestial creatures of Chinese myth. It represents the direction west, the season of autumn, and the element of metal. He is believed to be the king of all beasts.

4. At the start of each turn, if both Deep Wounds and Bite Marks have been inflicted, Byakko will activate <color=#72C5FF>Prey</color>, dealing heavy damage and inflicting <color=#72C5FF>Despair</color> on the target.
5. Every 2 turns, Byakko selects 1 Sudama as Bait, and on the next turn, eats the Sudama, fully restoring its HP and granting itself a buff.

name: Byakko
desc: One of the Ssu-Ling, celestial creatures of Chinese myth. It represents the direction west, the season of autumn, and the element of metal. He is believed to be the king of all beasts.

desc: A sun deity who was worshipped in the Roman Empire from the 1st to the 4th century AD. He was said to be reborn after death, and a festival was held on the winter solstice for him.

name: Mithras

name: Dakini
desc: Hindu deities of passion and relations. They are Kali's attendants. They eat human flesh and gather at graveyards and crematories each night. Their name means "sky dancer."

name: Apsaras
desc: Hindu water spirits, they are beautiful young women who dance for the gods. They also guide heroes fallen in battle to paradise.

name: Bugs

name: Oni
desc: An evil monster from Japanese lore known for its hideous visage and brute strength. They loot and plunder villages, massacring the townspeople with their iron clubs. They have horns on their heads, red skin, long claws, and razor-sharp teeth.

name: Pazuzu
desc: The Babylonian lord of wind and scorching sands. He has the body of a man, a lion's head, the claws and wings of an eagle, and has a deadly poison. The diseases he spreads can only be cured with magic.

name: Sudama
desc: A spirit of rivers and mountains in Japanese lore, it dwells in ancient trees and ageless rocks. They are not evil, and will often appear as humans or supernatural wonders to warn people.

name: Kumbhanda
desc: A Buddhist demon said to drain human life energy. He has dark skin, stands three meters tall, and sometimes changes his shape to a gourd. Known to have once served Rudra, the god of storms.

name: Isis
desc: Osiris's wife as well as his younger sister. Upon the death of her husband, she revived him with her incredible magic power. Isis is seen at many gravesites as the guardian goddess of the dead.

name: Hecatoncheires
desc: Giants born from Uranus and Gaia. The name means "those with a hundred arms." During the war of the Titans, Zeus freed them from the Underworld to help him obtain victory.

name: Kushinada
desc: A Japanese goddess. She governs fields and fertility. All of her sisters were sacrificed to Yamata-no-Orochi, but she was saved by Susano-o and became his wife.

name: Suzaku
desc: One of the Ssu-Ling, celestial creatures in Chinese myth. It is a giant bird that is said to chirp in five beautiful voices. It represents the direction south, the season of summer, and the element of fire.

name: Girimehkala
desc: A giant elephant monster of Sri Lankan myth, it is typically portrayed as being ridden by the Evil One, Mara. Whoever looks into its evil eye is said to be met with misfortune.

name: Surt
desc: A fire giant in Norse lore. He rules the fire realm, Muspelheim, and brandishes a burning sword. At Ragnarok, he will set the world ablaze.

strategy:

strategy: Each turn, Shadows will fire off a Death Stare at a random Phantom Thief. They will prioritize attacking the Phantom Thief under the Death Stare. By using Taunt skills or skills that increase their own attack taken rate, a Phantom Thief can transfer the Death Stare to themself.

name: Lilith
desc: Said to have been Adam's first wife, she desired to be his equal and refused to obey him. She was cast out of Eden and became a demon of the night. She is the mother of the demoness, Lilim.
strategy:
1. At the start of battle, Lilith summons 4 servants.
Lilith and all servants are in the <color=#ff3b37>Soul Link</color> state.
Soul Link: Distribute all damage received between all Shadows who share this condition, based on the percentage of their current HP.
2. Each turn, Lilith grants 1 Cover of Night stack to all Shadows.
Cover of Night: Decrease final damage taken by 15% for each stack. Stacks up to 2 times.
3. When a Shadow with Cover of Night is inflicted with an elemental ailment, remove 1 Cover of Night stack.

name: Nue
desc: A creature of Japanese lore with a monkey's head, tiger's legs, and snake's tail. The Tale of Heike says it hid behind a dark cloud each night to attack the Emperor.

name: Seiryu
desc: The noblest of the Ssu-Ling creatures of Chinese myth. It represents the direction east, the season of spring, and the element of wood. It dwells in a palace at the bottom of the ocean.
strategy:
1. At the start of battle, Seiryu gains 2 Azure Scales stacks, and gains 1 more stack every turn. Each stack decreases damage taken by 15%.
2. When Seiryu takes weakness damage, it loses 1 Azure Scales stack.
3. When Seiryu loses all Azure Scales stacks, all Phantom Thieves gain Seiryu's Might, increasing their damage.

name: Sraosha
desc: In Zoroastrian lore, Sraosha's duty is to listen to the cry of humans for Ahura Mazda. He is also known to descend after sunset to vanquish evil. His name literally means "observance."
strategy:
1. Sraosha will summon servants during the battle. When a servant is defeated, Sraosha takes Almighty damage based on the servant's max HP.
2. Sraosha will restore all Phantom Thieves' SP each turn, but also uses Debilitate on the Phantom Thief with the highest Attack, greatly decreasing their damage.
3. When a servant loses a Down Point, all Phantom Thieves' damage is increased by 15%. Lasts for 1 turn.

desc: Repeller of evil found at Kinpusen by En-no-Ozunu. Believed to be a fusion of Buddha, Guanyin, and Maitreya, he's a god who originated from Japan rather than the Buddhavacana.

3. When Zaou-Gongen loses all Vajra Shield stacks, all Phantom Thieves gain Demon Power, increasing their damage.

name: Regent
desc: A bluish-tinged diamond that Napoleon Bonaparte had mounted to the pommel of his sword. It was named after the French Regent Philippe II, Duke of Orleans, who had purchased it in 1717.

name: Queen's Necklace
desc: The diamond necklace that Jeanne de la Motte swindled from jewelers in 1785 by claiming it was on behalf of the Queen of France, Marie Antoinette.

name: Koh-i-Noor
desc: Once called the world's largest diamond, it was cut when it came to the British royal family. It is said to bring bad luck to any man who wears it, so only the females have ever adorned it.

name: Orlov
desc: A diamond stolen from a Hindu temple that is said to drive its owner to their death. It was cut into smaller pieces in an attempt to break the curse.

name: Alice
desc: A mysterious blond girl. She is quite powerful, despite her looks. Some say she is the ghost of a girl who died a sad death. Others say she is a spirit born from someone's imagination.

name: Futsunushi
desc: The Nihonshoki sword deity who pacified Ashihara-no-Nakatsukuni. His name comes from "futsu," the fashion in which things are cut, and "nushi," his nature as a god.

name: Yoshitsune
desc: A Japanese general of the Genpei War near the end of the Heian era and start of the Kamakura era. His bold ingenuity and ruthless skill with a blade are still praised in Japan today.

name: Beelzebub
desc: Demonic Lord of the Flies whose insect minions carry souls for him to control. He is mentioned in the Bible as a leader of evil spirits and is seen as a powerful demon.

name: Abaddon
desc: The "Destroyer" and "Angel of the Bottomless Pit" as described in ancient scriptures. He controls locusts, using them to cause massive destruction to villages.

name: Anubis
desc: The jackal-headed god of the dead and embalming from Egyptian myth. He weighs the hearts of the dead to determine their final destination.

name: Seth
desc: The Egyptian god of the desert, chaos, and evil. He murdered his brother, Osiris, and tried to become chief god, but he was castrated by Osiris's son, Horus.

name: Thoth
desc: Egyptian moon god that takes the form of a baboon, he is the one who measures time. He gave Isis the power to resurrect Osiris after he was killed by the evil god Seth.

name: Horus
desc: An ancient god of Egypt whose eyes are the sun and moon. Revered by some as the chief god, he is often depicted as a hawk or a falcon.

name: Zaou-Gongen
desc: Repeller of evil found at Kinpusen by En-no-Ozunu. Believed to be a fusion of Buddha, Guanyin, and Maitreya, he's a god who originated from Japan rather than the Buddhavacana.

name: Sraosha

name: Slime

name: Fuu-Ki

name: Anzu

name: Take-Minakata

name: Unicorn

name: Unicorn

name: Sui-Ki

name: Kin-Ki

name: Setanta

name: Leanan Sidhe

name: Atropos

name: Mithras

name: Kikuri-Hime

name: Lilith

name: Rakshasa
desc: A Hindu demon. He is an enemy of the gods and attacks humans to feed off of them. His hideous appearance strikes fear into those who see him. Rakshasa shape-shifts to deceive his enemies.

name: Hecatoncheires
desc: Giants born from Uranus and Gaia. The name means "those with a hundred arms." During the war of the Titans, Zeus freed them from the Underworld to help him obtain victory.

name: Pazuzu
desc: The Babylonian lord of wind and scorching sands. He has the body of a man, a lion's head, the claws and wings of an eagle, and has a deadly poison. The diseases he spreads can only be cured with magic.

name: Rangda
desc: A wicked witch of Balinese lore, she represents evil and is Barong's eternal rival. Even if defeated, she will come back to life, and their battle will have no end.

name: Ose
desc: One of the 72 demons of the Goetia, he is known as the President of Hell. He can shape-shift from leopard to human and reveal the truth behind divine mysteries.

name: Nekomata
desc: Long-lived cats are said to become these malevolent cat demons. Their powers vary according to how long they have lived, ranging from shape-shifting to controlling the dead.

name: Seth
desc: The Egyptian god of the desert, chaos, and evil. He murdered his brother, Osiris, and tried to become chief god, but he was castrated by Osiris's son, Horus.

name: Baphomet
desc: A goat-headed demon that is worshipped in Black Sabbaths. His name can be used as a catch-all term for demons in general. He would become an object of worship for witches.

name: Girimehkala

name: Pale Rider
desc: One of the Four Horsemen of the Apocalypse, he rides a pale horse and represents death. He has the power to destroy life.

name: Red Rider
desc: One of the Four Horsemen of the Apocalypse, he rides a red horse and carries a great sword. He has the power to destroy peace and make men slay one another.

name: Cu Chulainn
desc: A hero in Celtic folklore. He was called Setanta until he earned the name, "Culann's Hound." There are many tales of his adventures. He received his spear, Gae Bolg, from his mentor, Scathach.

name: Nebiros
desc: The general of Hell. He keeps watch over other demons. One of Hell's greatest necromancers, he can control souls and corpses.

name: Nebiros

name: Beelzebub

name: Naga

name: Lamia
desc: A half-human, half-snake female monster of Greek myth, she was once the queen of Libya. Zeus's jealous wife, Hera, killed her children, causing her to go mad and transform into a monster.

name: Lilim
desc: A demon who tempts sleeping men and attacks infants. She is the daughter of the demoness, Lilith. Like her mother, she drains men of their essence.

desc: A beautiful Hindu goddess of love and one of Shiva's wives. Always by his side, she played a role in opening his third eye. She can turn into Durga or Kali when angered.

desc: One of the four major archangels, his name means "healer." He recites the history of the fallen angels and the creation of Adam and Eve.

name: Kali
desc: A goddess of death and destruction. She is said to be another face of Parvati. She is violent, wears a string of skulls, and carries bloody weapons, but she also blesses her followers.

name: Yaksini
desc: A female demon in Hindu lore. Though originally a Dravidian fertility goddess, the spread of Hinduism changed perception of her to a demonic figure. Usually depicted as a nude, voluptuous female.

desc: One of the four major archangels. She is also the only female angel at this rank. Her name comes from the Sumerian word for "governor." She is the angel who told Mary of her pregnancy.

name: Sraosha
desc: In Zoroastrian lore, Sraosha's duty is to listen to the cry of humans for Ahura Mazda. He is also known to descend after sunset to vanquish evil. His name literally means "observance."

desc: The fourth of the nine orders of angels. Their duty is to oversee the other angels. Their actions are the manifestation of God's will.

Weaknesses and resistances are different than normal.
Dominion, Power, Principality, and Archangel have <color=#72C5FF>Soul Link</color>.

name: Kohryu
desc: Known as the Gold Dragon, it reigns over the Ssu-Ling, celestial creatures of Chinese lore. It is located at the center of the four beasts.
strategy:
During battle, Kohryu will summon Shade of Seiryu, Shade of Byakko, Shade of Suzaku, and Shade of Genbu. When a Shadow is summoned, its corresponding Might is granted to all Shadows on the field. When a Shadow is defeated, the Shadows lose that Might and it is granted to all Phantom Thieves instead.
Seiryu's Might: Grants a shield equal to 10% of max HP every turn.
Byakko's Might: Increases Attack by 20%.
Suzaku's Might: Increases damage dealt by 20%.
Genbu's Might: Increases Defense by 20%.

name: Surt
desc: A fire giant in Norse lore. He rules the fire realm, Muspelheim, and brandishes a burning sword. At Ragnarok, he will set the world ablaze.
strategy:
1. Surt grants <color=#72C5FF>Ragnarok</color> to all Shadows each turn.
Ragnarok: Increase damage by 5%, and lose a set amount of HP each turn. Stacks up to 10 times.
2. When Weakened, Surt grants 5 <color=#72C5FF>Ragnarok</color> stacks to all Phantom Thieves, and summons 4 Jack-o'-Lanterns. Damage dealt to the Jack-o'-Lanterns is added to your score.

name: Vishnu
desc: One of the major Hindu gods, he is the preserver and protector of the universe. Legends claim that he will make ten appearances across time and space to strike down evil and uphold justice.
strategy:
When Vishnu's HP falls below 90% or 60% for the first time, it summons 2 Avatars. The Avatars and Vishnu's main body are in the <color=#72C5FF>Soul Link</color> state.
Soul Link: Distributes all damage received between all Shadows who share this condition, based on the percentage of their current HP.

name: Atavaka
desc: One of the eight Yashaou. His domain is war and protection. Once a child-eating demon, he became one of the greatest of the Wisdom Kings after the Buddha converted him to good.
strategy:
Atavaka has different weaknesses and resistances than normal.
When Atavaka takes damage from a skill, it gains a Mark based on that skill's <color=#FF423F>attribute</color>. The maximum number of Marks is 7.
When it has collected 3 Marks of the same attribute, Atavaka spends all Marks to summon a Rakshasa. When Rakshasa is defeated, the corresponding attribute damage of all Phantom Thieves is increased. Atavaka can summon Rakshasa up to 2 times.

name: Atavaka
desc: One of the eight Yashaou. His domain is war and protection. Once a child-eating demon, he became one of the greatest of the Wisdom Kings after the Buddha converted him to good.
strategy:
Atavaka has different weaknesses and resistances than normal.
When Atavaka takes damage from a skill, it gains a Mark based on that skill's <color=#FF423F>attribute</color>. The maximum number of Marks is 7.
When it has collected 3 Marks of the same attribute, Atavaka spends all Marks to summon a Rakshasa. When Rakshasa is defeated, the corresponding attribute damage of all Phantom Thieves is increased. Atavaka can summon Rakshasa up to 2 times.

name: Yatsufusa
desc: Seven days after its birth, a wolf killed its mother. Yoshizane Satomi later promised his daughter's hand if it could defeat the enemy, but after Yatsufusa's success, Yoshizane's retainer shot it dead.
strategy:
1. Yatsufusa will activate Eight Beads of Virtue. Eight Beads of Virtue: All affinities change to Resist, damage dealt increases, and damage taken decreases. It also summons 4 Shadows. When a Shadow is defeated, Yatsufusa is inflicted with the corresponding elemental ailment for 2 turns. Summoned Shadows have different weaknesses and resistances than normal.
2. When Yatsufusa is in the Eight Beads of Virtue state and is inflicted with all 4 types of elemental ailments, the Eight Beads of Virtue state is canceled and its Defense decreases.
3. When Yatsufusa is Weakened, all Shadows vanish, and the Eight Beads of Virtue state is canceled.

name: Saki Mitama
desc: One of the four aspects of Shinto thought, it brings great bounty from the hunt. It is said to aid in love, profit, and growth, and can create new paths.
strategy: When Saki Mitama is defeated, inflict Shock on Yatsufusa.

name: Nigi Mitama
desc: One of the four aspects of Shinto thought, it works gently to help maintain a calm mind. It is said to aid in one's relations and sociability, and can lead one in a positive direction.
strategy: When Nigi Mitama is defeated, inflict Freeze on Yatsufusa.

name: Kushi Mitama
desc: One of the four aspects of Shinto thought, it uses its power to bring blessings related to healing illnesses and staying healthy. It is said to have supernatural powers and cause mysterious events.
strategy: When Kushi Mitama is defeated, inflict Windswept on Yatsufusa.

name: Ara Mitama
desc: One of the four aspects of Shinto thought, it has the power to grant ferocity. It is said to aid in one's bravery, growth, and endeavors, though it can lead in a negative direction.
strategy: When Ara Mitama is defeated, inflict Burn on Yatsufusa.

name: Nidhoggr
desc: An evil dragon that gnaws on the roots of Yggdrasil, the World Tree. It rules over the evil snakes that live there. Capable of surviving Ragnarok by feeding on the slain corpses that drift to it.
strategy:
Nidhoggr and Yurlungur have different weaknesses and resistances than usual.
1. Nidhoggr and other Shadows are always in the <color=#72C5FF>Soul Link</color> state.
Soul Link: Distributes all damage received between all Shadows who share this condition, based on the percentage of their current HP.
2. Whenever Nidhoggr and other Shadows use skills, all skill targets are inflicted with 1 <color=#72C5FF>Poison</color> stack.
Poison: Cannot be removed. At the end of a turn, the Phantom Thieves lose a certain amount of HP for each stack, but also have their Attack increased by 10%. Stacks up to 3 times.

name: Baal
desc: The chief Semitic god who governs over fertility. He is the god of Canaan and brother and consort to the goddess Anat, who saved him from Mot.
strategy:
Baal has different weaknesses and resistances than normal.
1. When Baal takes skill damage or receives a debuff, it gains 1 <color=#72C5FF>Decline</color> stack.
Decline: Decreases Defense for 3 turns. Stacks up to 15 times.
2. Baal will start preparing, and on the next turn, it uses <color=#72C5FF>Divine Spear of Baal</color>, dealing heavy damage to 1 Phantom Thief. If Decline reaches 10 stacks while preparing, the preparation is canceled, and the attack changes to <color=#72C5FF>Cleave</color>. Baal's single-target attacks will prioritize Assassin or Sweeper Phantom Thieves.

name: Kartikeya
desc: A Hindu god of war, known as Skanda or Murugan. He rides atop a peacock called Paravani,with bow and arrow drawn. He commands the army of the gods and defeated the forces of Asura.
strategy:
1. Kartikeya leads its army of birds in a coordinated strike.
2. When Garuda and Jatayu take damage from a Phantom Thief, that Thief's damage increases by 4% for 3 turns. Stacks up to 5 times. When Horus and Yatagarasu take damage from a Phantom Thief, that Thief's pierce rate increases by 2% for 3 turns. Stacks up to 5 times.

name: Decarabia
desc: One of the 72 demons of the Goetia, this demon appears as a pentacle. Keeper of jewels and herbal lore, Decarabia is said to have the ability to shape-shift at will.
strategy:
1. When Decarabia takes <color=#FF423F>weakness damage</color>, it will permanently gain 1 <color=#72C5FF>Weakness</color> stack. Each <color=#72C5FF>Weakness</color> stack increases Decarabia's damage taken.
2. When Decarabia takes damage from an attribute other than its weakness, it will immediately use <color=#72C5FF>Agilao</color> against the attacker.

name: Courageous Spirit
strategy:
1. When Courageous Spirit is present, <color=#FF423F>Decarabia's weak affinity will change</color>.
2. When Courageous Spirit is defeated, Decarabia's weak affinity will return to normal.

name: Matador
desc: A master sportsman who entertains the audience in exchange for his own life: one mistake can mean death. Some believe that matadors who die while performing remain in this world.
strategy:
1. Matador's skillful footwork raises its evasion.
Mirage Step: 100% chance to avoid <color=#FF423F>normal attacks</color>.
Reverse Step: 100% chance to avoid <color=#FF423F>ranged attacks</color>.
Cape-Sweep Step: 100% chance to avoid <color=#FF423F>skill attacks</color>.
2. At the end of each turn, Matador gains <color=#FF423F>1 random Step effect</color> and 3 Capote stacks. It will lose 1 stack when taking damage.
3. If Matador has Capote when it takes action, it will use Estocada to deal heavy damage to 1 Phantom Thief.

name: Matador
desc: A master sportsman who entertains the audience in exchange for his own life: one mistake can mean death. Some believe that matadors who die while performing remain in this world.
strategy:
1. Matador's <color=#72C5FF>Master Step</color> gives it a 100% chance to dodge all attacks.
2. After a set amount of time, Matador summons Matador's Spirit, which will flee after 1 turn.
3. When Matador's Spirit is defeated, Matador loses motivation and the Master Step effect. It will also be unable to act for 2 turns. Afterwards, Matador regains its will to fight along with the Master Step effect.

name: Fuu-Ki
desc: One of the four oni controlled by Fujiwara no Chikata, it sends hurricanes to blow away its enemies. Some say that Fuu-ki is the original ninja.
strategy:
1. Fuu-Ki's <color=#72C5FF>Wind Domain</color> gives it a base chance of 80% to inflict <color=#72C5FF>Ultrawindswept</color> when attacking. Ultrawindswept lasts for 2 turns.
<color=#72C5FF>Ultrawindswept</color>: An enhanced version of Windswept inflicted by Fuu-Ki. Decreases Defense by 24%.
2. Fuu-Ki deals increased damage to Phantom Thieves in the <color=#72C5FF>Ultrawindswept</color> state.

name: Sui-Ki
desc: One of the four oni controlled by Fujiwara no Chikata, it can cause floods with the swing of its arms. In the Taiheiki, Ki no Tomoo expelled the oni by reading a Japanese poem.
strategy:
1. Sui-Ki's <color=#72C5FF>Ice Domain</color> gives it a base chance of 80% to inflict <color=#72C5FF>Ultrafreeze</color> when attacking. Ultrafreeze lasts for 2 turns.
<color=#72C5FF>Ultrafreeze</color>: An enhanced version of Frozen inflicted by Sui-Ki. Decreases Attack by 24%.
2. Sui-Ki deals increased damage to Phantom Thieves in the <color=#72C5FF>Ultrafreeze</color> state.

name: Kin-Ki
desc: One of the four oni controlled by Fujiwara no Chikata, its body is so hard that no weapons can penetrate it. It and its comrades fell into hell through holes that can still be found in modern Iga.
strategy:
1. Kin-Ki's <color=#FF3B37>Golden Domain</color> allows it to grant <color=#FF3B37>Indestructible Vajra</color> to 1 random Shadow after dealing damage.
<color=#FF3B37>Indestructible Vajra</color>: Nullifies the next damage taken.
2. When Kin-Ki has <color=#FF3B37>Indestructible Vajra</color>, its damage increases.

name: Nekomata
desc: Long-lived cats are said to become these malevolent cat demons. Their powers vary according to how long they have lived, ranging from shape-shifting to controlling the dead.

name: Nekomata
desc: Long-lived cats are said to become these malevolent cat demons. Their powers vary according to how long they have lived, ranging from shape-shifting to controlling the dead.

name: Ongyo-Ki
desc: One of the four oni controlled by Fujiwara no Chikata. By eliminating its aura and preventing others from sensing its presence, it is able to surprise its enemies.
strategy:
1. Ongyo-Ki starts with 3 <color=#72C5FF>Damage Reduction</color> stacks, which increases the damage dealt to Phantom Thieves with elemental ailments.
2. When Fuu-Ki, Sui-Ki, or Kin-Ki are defeated, Ongyo-Ki loses 1 <color=#72C5FF>Damage Reduction</color> stack. It then gains the Domain effect from the defeated Shadow, and its affinities change.

name: Setanta
desc: A brave young man in Celtic myth. After defeating a fierce guard dog, he volunteered to take its place, earning him the nickname "Hound of Culann."
strategy: When Setanta defeats a guard dog...

name: Inugami
desc: A dog spirit said to possess people in Japanese lore. Those possessed are in a state of "inu-tsuki" and lose consciousness. Onmyoji use Inugami as familiars.
strategy: A fierce guard dog that bites enemies and allies alike.

name: Cu Chulainn
desc: A hero in Celtic folklore. He was called Setanta until he earned the name, "Culann's Hound." There are many tales of his adventures. He received his spear, Gae Bolg, from his mentor, Scathach.
strategy: Cu Chulainn locks onto 1 Phantom Thief and activates <color=#72C5FF>Gae Bolg</color> on the next turn, dealing heavy damage and inflicting an insta-kill effect.

name: Setanta
desc: A brave young man in Celtic myth. After defeating a fierce guard dog, he volunteered to take its place, earning him the nickname "Hound of Culann."
strategy:
1. Leanan Sidhe grants 1 Growth stack to Setanta every turn. When Growth reaches 3 stacks, Setanta transforms into <color=#FF423F>Cu Chulainn</color>.
2. When Leanan Sidhe is defeated, Setanta gains 3 Growth stacks.
3. Cu Chulainn locks onto 1 Phantom Thief and activates <color=#72C5FF>Gae Bolg</color> on the next turn, dealing heavy damage and inflicting an insta-kill effect.

name: Leanan Sidhe
desc: A beautiful fairy of Irish lore that yearns for the love of a human man. She drains the life of her lovers in return for granting them artistic inspiration.
strategy:
1. Leanan Sidhe grants 1 Growth stack to Setanta every turn. When Growth reaches 3 stacks, Setanta transforms into <color=#FF423F>Cu Chulainn</color>.
2. When Leanan Sidhe is defeated, Setanta gains 3 Growth stacks.

name: Take-Minakata
desc: A Japanese god of war, hunting and fertility. He fought Take-Mikazuchi for control of Japan and lost. He escaped to Suwa, but has been prohibited to leave since then.
strategy:
1. Take-Minakata deals more damage the lower its HP is.
2. Whenever Take-Minakata uses a skill, it loses 20% of its current HP, and gains a shield equal to 20% of its max HP.
3. Every 3 turns, Take-Minakata summons 1 War God's Spirit. If it is defeated in 1 turn, all Phantom Thieves' Attack is increased. If it is not defeated in 1 turn, Take-Minakata absorbs the War God's Spirit, and gains a shield equal to 50% of its max HP.

name: War God's Spirit
strategy: A War God Spirit summoned by Take-Minakata.

name: Take-Minakata
desc: A Japanese god of war, hunting and fertility. He fought Take-Mikazuchi for control of Japan and lost. He escaped to Suwa, but has been prohibited to leave since then.
strategy:
1. Take-Minakata deals more damage the lower its HP is.
2. Take-Minakata will take 90% of the damage for other Shadows, and when it receives fatal damage, it will instead enter an Endure state, its HP will be fixed at 1, and will die after 2 turns.

name: Ame-no-Uzume
desc: Japanese goddess of entertainment, she governs many sacred dances. She is most famous for luring out Amaterasu, who had barricaded herself inside a cave.

name: Take-Minakata
desc: A Japanese god of war, hunting and fertility. He fought Take-Mikazuchi for control of Japan and lost. He escaped to Suwa, but has been prohibited to leave since then.
strategy:
1. Take-Minakata deals more damage the lower its HP is
2. When Take-Minakata's HP is low, it will summon 4 War God's Spirits, and after 1 turn absorb all of them. For each one absorbed, it restores 25% of its max HP. If the Phantom Thieves defeat all of the War God's Spirits, Take-Minakata will be defeated.

name: War God's Spirit

name: Leanan Sidhe
desc: A beautiful fairy of Irish lore that yearns for the love of a human man. She drains the life of her lovers in return for granting them artistic inspiration.
strategy:

name: Thoth
desc: Egyptian moon god that takes the form of a baboon, he is the one who measures time. He gave Isis the power to resurrect Osiris after he was killed by the evil god Seth.
strategy:
1. Thoth is the god of the Moon, and Horus is the god of the Sun. They govern over day and night respectively. If Thoth is attacked, it will become night. If Horus is attacked, it will become day.
2. During the day, Thoth's damage dealt is decreased by 70%, and its damage taken is increased by 70%. At night, its damage dealt is increased by 70%, and its damage taken is decreased by 70%. The effects of day and night on Horus are the opposite.

name: Horus
desc: An ancient god of Egypt whose eyes are the sun and moon. Revered by some as the chief god, he is often depicted as a hawk or a falcon.
strategy:
1. Thoth is the god of the Moon, and Horus is the god of the Sun. They govern over day and night respectively. If Thoth is attacked, it will become night. If Horus is attacked, it will become day.
2. During the day, Thoth's damage dealt is decreased by 70%, and its damage taken is increased by 70%. At night, its damage dealt is increased by 70%, and its damage taken is decreased by 70%. The effects of day and night on Horus are the opposite.

name: Thoth
desc: Egyptian moon god that takes the form of a baboon, he is the one who measures time. He gave Isis the power to resurrect Osiris after he was killed by the evil god Seth.
strategy:
1. Each turn, Thoth's affinity will change to Drain either an elemental attribute (Fire, Ice, Electric, or Wind) or spiritual attribute (Psychokinesis, Nuclear, Bless, or Curse). When it takes damage of a corresponding attribute group, it gains 1 Lunar Power stack.
2. When Thoth has 2 or more Lunar Power stacks, it will spend 2 Lunar Power to enter the <color=#72C5FF>Full Moon</color> state, increasing its own abilities and summoning 2 Sandmen.
3. Every 3 turns, Thoth will use Full Moon's Protection, entering a preparation state and gaining a shield. If the shield is destroyed before the next turn, the preparation is canceled. If it is not destroyed, Thoth immediately enters the <color=#72C5FF>Full Moon</color> state.

name: Thoth
desc: Egyptian moon god that takes the form of a baboon, he is the one who measures time. He gave Isis the power to resurrect Osiris after he was killed by the evil god Seth.
strategy:
1. The moon changes phases, starting with New Moon. It follows a sequence of New Moon, Waxing Crescent, Full Moon, and Waning Crescent.

New Moon: Damage dealt decreases by 50%, and damage taken increases by 50%.
Waxing Crescent: Damage dealt increases by 50%, and damage taken increases by 50%.
Full Moon: Damage dealt increases by 50%, and damage taken decreases by 50%.
Waning Crescent: Damage dealt decreases by 50%, and damage taken decreases by 50%.

name: Clock

name: Hell Biker
desc: A motorcyclist whose violent nature turned him into a demon. His anger with himself and the world causes him to lash out, that everyone else would suffer as well.
strategy:
1. At the end of each turn, Hell Biker will inflict Hellscorched on a random Phantom Thief.
Hellscorched: Lose a large amount of HP at the end of each turn. Stacks up to 3 times. Can be removed after taking <color=#FF423F>Ice</color> damage.
2. Victory is achieved when Hell Biker is defeated.

name: Jack Frost
desc: A winter fairy of European descent. He leaves ice patterns on windows and nips people's noses. Though normally an innocent creature, he will freeze his victims to death if provoked.
strategy: Jack Frost will not attack unprovoked and cannot be defeated. When damaged, he will immediately use <color=#72C5FF>Bufu</color> on the attacker, dealing a small amount of <color=#FF423F>Ice</color> damage.

name: Hell Biker
desc: A motorcyclist whose violent nature turned him into a demon. His anger with himself and the world causes him to lash out, that everyone else would suffer as well.
strategy:
At the end of each turn, Hell Biker will inflict Hellscorched on all Phantom Thieves.
Hellscorched: Lose a large amount of HP at the end of each turn. Stacks up to 3 times. Can be removed after taking <color=#FF423F>Ice</color> damage.

name: Jack Frost
desc: A winter fairy of European descent. He leaves ice patterns on windows and nips people's noses. Though normally an innocent creature, he will freeze his victims to death if provoked.
strategy: Jack Frost will not attack unprovoked. When defeated, he will immediately deal a small amount of <color=#FF423F>Ice</color> damage to all Phantom Thieves.

name: Unicorn
desc: A legendary white horse with a single spiral horn. It can only be tamed by a pure maiden, and its horn supposedly has miraculous healing capabilities.
strategy:
1. At the start of battle, Unicorn gains 5 <color=#72C5FF>Purity</color> stacks.
2. When Unicorn receives a buff or healing, it gains 1 more Purity stack.
Purity: Increases Attack and Defense. When Purity reaches 10 stacks, Unicorn unleashes its Holy Power.
Holy Power: Deals heavy damage to all Phantom Thieves and fully restores all Shadows' HP.
3. Every turn, Unicorn randomly summons Nigi Mitama, Saki Mitama, Kushi Mitama, or Ara Mitama, which each grant Unicorn various buffs.
4. When Unicorn takes <color=#FF423F>debuffs</color>, it loses 2 Purity stacks.

name: Saki Mitama
desc: One of the four aspects of Shinto thought, it brings great bounty from the hunt. It is said to aid in love, profit, and growth, and can create new paths.

name: Nigi Mitama
desc: One of the four aspects of Shinto thought, it works gently to help maintain a calm mind. It is said to aid in one's relations and sociability, and can lead one in a positive direction.

name: Kushi Mitama
desc: One of the four aspects of Shinto thought, it uses its power to bring blessings related to healing illnesses and staying healthy. It is said to have supernatural powers and cause mysterious events.

name: Ara Mitama
desc: One of the four aspects of Shinto thought, it has the power to grant ferocity. It is said to aid in one's bravery, growth, and endeavors, though it can lead in a negative direction.

name: Daisoujou
desc: A monk who died while fasting, his spiritual power allows his body to continue to exist without rotting. It is said that he will appear before people on the day of salvation.
strategy:
1. Daisoujou cannot be targeted by the Phantom Thieves, and cannot be defeated.
2. At the start of the battle, Daisoujou's HP is only 1% of the maximum, and each turn it will use <color=#72C5FF>Sokushin</color>. Sokushin: Deals Almighty damage to all Phantom Thieves based on their current HP percentage, and consumes a certain amount of SP. Also restores the same amount of HP to Daisoujou.
3. Onmoraki will continously appear on the field and deal a set amount of damage to Daisoujou.
4. Victory is acheived if Daisoujou's HP is healed to 100%. The battle is lost if Daisoujou's HP is too low. Quickly defeat the Onmoraki while protecting Daisoujou.

name: Onmoraki
desc: A monstrous, fire spitting, Japanese bird with a man's face. It is actually a corpse that was not given a proper memorial service. They appear before monks who neglect their duties.

3. At the start of the battle, Daisoujou has 1% of its max HP. Victory is acheived if Daisoujou's HP is healed to 100%. The battle is lost if Daisoujou's HP is too low.
4. <color=#72C5FF>Quickly defeat the Onmoraki</color> while <color=#72C5FF>protecting Daisoujou</color>.

name: Pazuzu
desc: The Babylonian lord of wind and scorching sands. He has the body of a man, a lion's head, the claws and wings of an eagle, and has a deadly poison. The diseases he spreads can only be cured with magic.
strategy:
1. Pazuzu's skills can inflict Plague Curse. Plague Curse: Deals damage equal to 5% of max HP at the end of the turn.
2. Pazuzu uses Spreading Sickness every other turn. Spreading Sickness: Inflicts 2 Plague Curse stacks on all Phantom Thieves, with a high chance of inflicting spiritual ailments.
3. Pazuzu uses Eternal Binding every turn. Eternal Binding: Inflicts 2 Plague Curse stacks on all Phantom Thieves, and immediately activates Plague Curse 1 time.

name: Pale Rider
desc: One of the Four Horsemen of the Apocalypse, he rides a pale horse and represents death. He has the power to destroy life.
strategy: When Pale Rider attacks, it inflicts 1 Plague Curse stack on Shadows. While Pale Rider is present, Pazuzu's final damage taken is decreased by 30%.

name: Hua Po

name: Phoenix
desc: The legendary bird of Chinese myth, said to appear only in times of peace. It is the ruler of all birds. When it dies, birds across the land chirp with sadness.

name: Isis
desc: Osiris's wife as well as his younger sister. Upon the death of her husband, she revived him with her incredible magic power. Isis is seen at many gravesites as the guardian goddess of the dead.

name: Sudama
desc: A spirit of rivers and mountains in Japanese lore, it dwells in ancient trees and ageless rocks. They are not evil, and will often appear as humans or supernatural wonders to warn people.

name: Orobas
desc: One of the 72 demons of the Goetia. Known as the Prince of Hell, he appears as a horse and answers questions of the past, present, and future. He is faithful to his conjurer.

name: Angel
desc: The ninth of the nine orders of angels. They are closest in nature to humans. They watch over individuals and warn those who stray from the path.

name: Mokoi

name: Jatayu
desc: The Hindu king of birds. In the Ramayana, he fought bravely against Ravana in an attempt to save Sita, Rama's wife and the seventh avatar of Vishnu, but lost.

name: Mitra
desc: An ancient Persian god of contracts. He was also revered as a harvest-bringing sun god when he was introduced to the Zoroastrian religion.

name: Setanta
desc: A brave young man in Celtic myth. After defeating a fierce guard dog, he volunteered to take its place, earning him the nickname "Hound of Culann."

name: Take-Minakata
desc: A Japanese god of war, hunting and fertility. He fought Take-Mikazuchi for control of Japan and lost. He escaped to Suwa, but has been prohibited to leave since then.

name: Isis
desc: Osiris's wife as well as his younger sister. Upon the death of her husband, she revived him with her incredible magic power. Isis is seen at many gravesites as the guardian goddess of the dead.

name: Clotho
desc: The youngest of the three Moirae Sisters of Greek legend. She spins the threads of life with her spindle.

name: Jikokuten
desc: Also known as Dhritarashtra, he is the protector of the East, and is one of the four Heavenly Kings of Buddhist origin. He helps maintain the security of the nation.

name: Flauros
desc: One of the 72 demons of the Goetia. He appears as a leopard and can see the past and future. He can control fire and burn all his adversaries to death.

name: Kurama Tengu
desc: A type of tengu said to have lived on Mt. Kurama in Kyoto. The most powerful and well-known of the tengu, they have the power to fend off disease and bring good fortune.

name: Belphegor
desc: Demonic governor of the deadly sin of sloth. He also excels at invention and discovery. May be derived from Ba'al Pe'or, Syrian god of abundant crops.

name: Hariti
desc: Also known as Kishimojin, she once ate children, but stopped after Buddha changed her ways. She now eats pomegranates and is a goddess of parenting.

name: Rangda
desc: A wicked witch of Balinese lore, she represents evil and is Barong's eternal rival. Even if defeated, she will come back to life, and their battle will have no end.

name: Quetzalcoatl
desc: An Aztec deity known as the Feathered Serpent. He created humans with his own blood and taught them how to sustain themselves.

name: Sarasvati
desc: The Hindu goddess of rivers, and patron of speech, writing, learning, the arts, and sciences. Brahma is her husband.

name: Baphomet
desc: A goat-headed demon that is worshipped in Black Sabbaths. His name can be used as a catch-all term for demons in general. He would become an object of worship for witches.

name: Yatagarasu
desc: A divine creature in Japanese lore. They are three-legged birds sent by Amaterasu to help humans. They are said to have helped Emperor Jinmu claim victory.

name: Horus
desc: An ancient god of Egypt whose eyes are the sun and moon. Revered by some as the chief god, he is often depicted as a hawk or a falcon.

name: Rangda
desc: A wicked witch of Balinese lore, she represents evil and is Barong's eternal rival. Even if defeated, she will come back to life, and their battle will have no end.

name: Moloch
desc: A Canaanite god of fire. A bronze statue of a man with a bull's head stands at his altar. The statue was heated and sacrificial children were thrown inside.

name: Barong
desc: A mystical creature in Balinese lore, it represents good and is Rangda's eternal rival. Even if defeated, it will be reborn. The result is a never-ending struggle.

name: Quetzalcoatl
desc: An Aztec deity known as the Feathered Serpent. He created humans with his own blood and taught them how to sustain themselves.

name: Principality
desc: The seventh of the nine orders of angels. They guard cities and nations, and protect various religious figures.

name: Nebiros
desc: The general of Hell. He keeps watch over other demons. One of Hell's greatest necromancers, he can control souls and corpses.

name: Bugs
desc: A Welsh creature commonly known as "Bugbear" or the "Boogeyman." Its existence is often used by mothers to scare children into behaving.

name: Mothman
desc: A cryptid sighted during the 60sâ€“80s in West Virginia. It has shining red eyes and is named for the fin-like appendages on its sides. It uses its keen sense for blood to track down the source and feed on it.

name: Raja Naga
desc: The king of the Naga, a half-man, half-snake tribe in Hindu lore. The dragon kings Nanda and Takshaka of Buddhist myth fall into this royal category.

name: Genbu
desc: One of the Ssu-Ling, celestial creatures of Chinese myth. It represents the direction north, the season of winter, and the element of water. Known to be a great warrior, it supports the Earth from below.

name: Bicorn
desc: An evil creature with two curving horns from European folklore. It represents impurity, unlike the Unicorn. Said to be derived from Re'em in the Bible. Another legend says that it feeds off of loyal husbands.

name: Eligor
desc: One of the 72 demons of the Goetia. He looks like a knight and has the power to see things to come. He also knows much about war.

name: Ippon-Datara
desc: A one-eyed, one-legged monster said to live deep in the mountains of Kumano, Japan. It's believed to be the degraded blacksmith god, Ame no Me-Hitotsu no Kami.

name: Archangel
desc: The eighth of the nine orders of angels. Their duty is to minister to humans and deliver messages. They are warriors of Heaven and lead Heaven's forces during battle with the armies of evil.

name: Angel
desc: The ninth of the nine orders of angels. They are closest in nature to humans. They watch over individuals and warn those who stray from the path.

name: Oni
desc: An evil monster from Japanese lore known for its hideous visage and brute strength. They loot and plunder villages, massacring the townspeople with their iron clubs. They have horns on their heads, red skin, long claws, and razor-sharp teeth.

name: Leanan Sidhe
desc: A beautiful fairy of Irish lore that yearns for the love of a human man. She drains the life of her lovers in return for granting them artistic inspiration.

name: Apsaras
desc: Hindu water spirits, they are beautiful young women who dance for the gods. They also guide heroes fallen in battle to paradise.

name: Agathion
desc: A general term for familiars used by Judeo-Christian magicians, they are usually sealed away in bottles, rings, or talismans. They torment the target selected by the conjuror.

name: Yaksini
desc: A female demon in Hindu lore. Though originally a Dravidian fertility goddess, the spread of Hinduism changed perception of her to a demonic figure. Usually depicted as a nude, voluptuous female.

name: Eligor
desc: One of the 72 demons of the Goetia. He looks like a knight and has the power to see things to come. He also knows much about war.
