name: Anubis
desc: The jackal-headed god of the dead and embalming from Egyptian myth. He weighs the hearts of the dead to determine their final destination.

name: Unicorn
desc: A legendary white horse with a single spiral horn. It can only be tamed by a pure maiden, and its horn supposedly has miraculous healing capabilities.

name: Neko Shogun
desc: A prophetic Taoist god, originally known as Mao Shogun. Due to a linguistic error involving the Chinese word for "cat," his name was changed to Neko Shogun.

name: Hell Biker
desc: A motorcyclist whose violent nature turned him into a demon. His anger with himself and the world causes him to lash out, that everyone else would suffer as well.

name: Daisoujou
desc: A monk who died while fasting, his spiritual power allows his body to continue to exist without rotting. It is said that he will appear before people on the day of salvation.

name: Okuninushi
desc: A Kunitsu deity in Japanese mythology that governs agriculture and medicine. He's said to have built the country of Izumo with Susano-o's daughter, Suseri-Hime.

name: Nigi Mitama
desc: One of the four aspects of Shinto thought, it works gently to help maintain a calm mind. It is said to aid in one's relations and sociability, and can lead one in a positive direction.

name: Ara Mitama
desc: One of the four aspects of Shinto thought, it has the power to grant ferocity. It is said to aid in one's bravery, growth, and endeavors, though it can lead in a negative direction.

name: Kushi Mitama
desc: One of the four aspects of Shinto thought, it uses its power to bring blessings related to healing illnesses and staying healthy. It is said to have supernatural powers and cause mysterious events.

name: Pazuzu
desc: The Babylonian lord of wind and scorching sands. He has the body of a man, a lion's head, the claws and wings of an eagle, and has a deadly poison. The diseases he spreads can only be cured with magic.

name: Belphegor
desc: Demonic governor of the deadly sin of sloth. He also excels at invention and discovery. May be derived from Ba'al Pe'or, Syrian god of abundant crops.

name: Daisoujou
desc: A monk who died while fasting, his spiritual power allows his body to continue to exist without rotting. It is said that he will appear before people on the day of salvation.

name: Anubis
desc: The jackal-headed god of the dead and embalming from Egyptian myth. He weighs the hearts of the dead to determine their final destination.

name: Zouchouten
desc: Also known as Virudhaka, he is the protector of the South, and is one of the four Heavenly Kings of Buddhist origin. He is the god of the five grains, and was once the chief of the gods.

name: Ame-no-Uzume
desc: Japanese goddess of entertainment, she governs many sacred dances. She is most famous for luring out Amaterasu, who had barricaded herself inside a cave.

name: Cu Chulainn
desc: A hero in Celtic folklore. He was called Setanta until he earned the name, "Culann's Hound." There are many tales of his adventures. He received his spear, Gae Bolg, from his mentor, Scathach.

name: Cerberus
desc: The guardian hound who prevents anyone from entering or exiting the underworld in Greek lore. It was born from Typhon and Echidna, and is the older brother of Orthrus.

name: Ongyo-Ki
desc: One of the four oni controlled by Fujiwara no Chikata. By eliminating its aura and preventing others from sensing its presence, it is able to surprise its enemies.

name: Black Frost
desc: A Jack Frost that yearned for evil. This powerful demon is born when a cute Jack Frost remembers its demonic nature.

name: Kohryu
desc: Known as the Gold Dragon, it reigns over the Ssu-Ling, celestial creatures of Chinese lore. It is located at the center of the four beasts.

name: Seiryu
desc: The noblest of the Ssu-Ling creatures of Chinese myth. It represents the direction east, the season of spring, and the element of wood. It dwells in a palace at the bottom of the ocean.

name: Byakko
desc: One of the Ssu-Ling, celestial creatures of Chinese myth. It represents the direction west, the season of autumn, and the element of metal. He is believed to be the king of all beasts.

name: Suzaku
desc: One of the Ssu-Ling, celestial creatures in Chinese myth. It is a giant bird that is said to chirp in five beautiful voices. It represents the direction south, the season of summer, and the element of fire.

name: Genbu
desc: One of the Ssu-Ling, celestial creatures of Chinese myth. It represents the direction north, the season of winter, and the element of water. Known to be a great warrior, it supports the Earth from below.

name: Oberon
desc: The king of the fairies and Titania's husband. He is quite old but, due to a curse, his looks are that of a young boy. He often flirts with human women, which sometimes earns him a scolding from his wife.

name: Titania
desc: The queen of the fairies and Oberon's wife. She is derived from the Roman goddess Diana. She was later immortalized in Shakespeare's play "A Midsummer Night's Dream."

name: Thor
desc: The Norse thunder god and son of Odin, Thor owns the power-enhancing belt Megingjard and wields Mjolnir, a hammer that causes lightning to strike and returns to its owner if thrown.

name: Surt
desc: A fire giant in Norse lore. He rules the fire realm, Muspelheim, and brandishes a burning sword. At Ragnarok, he will set the world ablaze.

name: Sandalphon
desc: Metatron's twin brother in Judeo-Christian lore, he is the master of heavenly songs. It is said that a human would take 500 years to walk the length of his body.

name: Cerberus
desc: The guardian hound who prevents anyone from entering or exiting the underworld in Greek lore. It was born from Typhon and Echidna, and is the older brother of Orthrus.

name: Lakshmi
desc: The Hindu goddess of beauty and good fortune, Vishnu's wife, and Kama's mother. She is the goddess of love, believed to have been born from an ocean of milk.

name: Ganesha
desc: The Hindu elephant-headed god. He was originally created by Parvati in order to prevent anyone from watching her bathe. Shiva batted off his original head and replaced it with an elephant's head.

name: Dominion
desc: The fourth of the nine orders of angels. Their duty is to oversee the other angels. Their actions are the manifestation of God's will.

name: Norn
desc: Goddesses of fate in Norse lore. They live below the roots of Yggdrasil and weave the threads of fate, which even the gods are bound by.

name: Power
desc: The sixth of the nine orders of angels. It is said that they were the first order to be created. Their duty is to protect human souls from demons.
strategy:
1. When Shadows on the field use a certain skill, all Shadows gain <color=#72C5FF>Legion</color>.
2. When <color=#72C5FF>Legion</color> reaches 5 stacks, Power will activate a powerful multi-target attack skill.
3. When there are less than 2 Principalities on the field, Power will spend all <color=#72C5FF>Legion</color> stacks to summon 2 Principalities. It can summon a maximum of 2 times during the battle.

name: Principality
desc: The seventh of the nine orders of angels. They guard cities and nations, and protect various religious figures.

name: Ose
desc: One of the 72 demons of the Goetia, he is known as the President of Hell. He can shape-shift from leopard to human and reveal the truth behind divine mysteries.
strategy:
1. When Ose activates <color=#72C5FF>Revenge Stance</color>, it enters a Counterattack Stance and will counterattack when it takes damage. <color=#72C5FF>Revenge Stance</color> lasts for 2 turns. When a counterattack is successful, Attack increases.
2. After <color=#72C5FF>Revenge Stance</color> ends, targets who took counterattacks from Ose will be Taunted.

name: Arahabaki
desc: A mysterious god of ancient Japan. Most famously worshipped by Nagasunehiko, who was defeated in battle against Emperor Jinmu, Arahabaki came to be treated as a symbol of rebellion and defiance.

name: Byakko
desc: One of the Ssu-Ling, celestial creatures of Chinese myth. It represents the direction west, the season of autumn, and the element of metal. He is believed to be the king of all beasts.
strategy:
1. Byakko's <color=#72C5FF>Vicious Bite</color> skill will inflict <color=#72C5FF>Deep Wounds</color> on all Phantom Thieves, decreasing their Defense and increasing their damage taken. Use the Guard command to remove the <color=#72C5FF>Deep Wounds</color> condition.
2. Byakko's <color=#72C5FF>Sharp Claws</color> skill will target the Phantom Thief with the lowest HP, and if they have <color=#72C5FF>Deep Wounds</color>, the damage is increased. When this skill KO's a Phantom Thief, it immediately activates again.

name: Lamia
desc: A half-human, half-snake female monster of Greek myth, she was once the queen of Libya. Zeus's jealous wife, Hera, killed her children, causing her to go mad and transform into a monster.

name: King Frost
desc: The king of snow who rules over an infinite number of Jack Frosts. He has the power to freeze the entire world, but is unaware of it due to his naÃ¯ve personality.
strategy:
1. King Frost will not attack, but will continously summon shadows. When all the summoned shadows are defeated, King Frost loses 30% HP.
2. The longer the summoned shadows stay on the field, the more their Attack and Defense will increase.

name: Jack Frost
desc: A winter fairy of European descent. He leaves ice patterns on windows and nips people's noses. Though normally an innocent creature, he will freeze his victims to death if provoked.

name: Black Frost
desc: A Jack Frost that yearned for evil. This powerful demon is born when a cute Jack Frost remembers its demonic nature.

name: Black Rider
desc: One of the Four Horsemen of the Apocalypse, he rides a black horse and carries scales. He brings famine and has the right to end lives through suffering.
strategy:
1. When Black Rider or Pale Rider take fatal damage, they survive with 1 HP and enter a <color=#72C5FF>False Death</color> state. If both enter the False Death state at the same time, they are defeated.
2. If either Black Rider or Pale Rider are in a <color=#72C5FF>False Death</color> state at the start of the turn, the other will use a skill to revive them. This will also increase their Attack and max HP.
3. Black Rider's ability, <color=#72C5FF>Black Dance</color>: Increase the damage dealt by both Riders and decrease their damage taken. Effect lasts until either Rider is defeated.
<color=#72C5FF>Monochrome Rondeau: Black</color>: After reviving 2 or more times, the Riders will activate Monochrome Rondeau: Black, dealing heavy multi-target damage and inflicting Forget on the Phantom Thief with the lowest current HP.

name: Pale Rider
desc: One of the Four Horsemen of the Apocalypse, he rides a pale horse and represents death. He has the power to destroy life.
strategy:
1. When Black Rider or Pale Rider take fatal damage, they survive with 1 HP and enter a <color=#72C5FF>False Death</color> state. If both enter the False Death state at the same time, they are defeated.
2. If either Black Rider or Pale Rider are in a <color=#72C5FF>False Death</color> state at the start of the turn, the other will use a skill to revive them. This will also increase their Attack and max HP.
3. Pale Rider's ability, <color=#72C5FF>White Dance</color>: Deals a set amount of damage to the Phantom Thief with the lowest Defense, and locks on.
<color=#72C5FF>Monochrome Rondeau: White</color>: On the next turn after using <color=#72C5FF>White Dance</color>, deals heavy damage to the Phantom Thief that was locked on to with <color=#72C5FF>White Dance</color>, if neither Rider is in the <color=#72C5FF>False Death</color> state.

name: Surt
desc: A fire giant in Norse lore. He rules the fire realm, Muspelheim, and brandishes a burning sword. At Ragnarok, he will set the world ablaze.

name: Valkyrie
desc: "Choosers of the slain" in Norse lore. Armed with shining armor and swords, they look for brave warriors to take to Valhalla, so that they may fight in Ragnarok.

name: Oberon
desc: The king of the fairies and Titania's husband. He is quite old but, due to a curse, his looks are that of a young boy. He often flirts with human women, which sometimes earns him a scolding from his wife.
strategy:
When either Oberon or Titania is defeated, the other will be unable to act for 2 turns.
After they recover, their damage will be <color=#FF423F>significantly increased</color>.

desc: A drunkard who tricked the Devil out of taking him to Hell. When refused entry to Heaven, he was forced to wander the earth with only an ember as a light.

desc: The Egyptian god of the desert, chaos, and evil. He murdered his brother, Osiris, and tried to become chief god, but he was castrated by Osiris's son, Horus.

name: Regent
desc: A bluish-tinged diamond that Napoleon Bonaparte had mounted to the pommel of his sword. It was named after the French Regent Philippe II, Duke of Orleans, who had purchased it in 1717.

Soul Link: When a Shadow with Soul Link takes damage, split the damage between all Shadows with Soul Link, based on its current HP.
Sanctuary: Increase damage taken by 6% per <color=#FFFC40>debuff</color> inflicted, up to 30%.

desc: A hero in Celtic folklore. He was called Setanta until he earned the name, "Culann's Hound." There are many tales of his adventures. He received his spear, Gae Bolg, from his mentor, Scathach.
strategy:
1. Cu Chulainn's <color=#FF423F>critical damage taken</color> is increased by 30%, and its non-critical damage taken is decreased by 50%.
2. Cu Chulainn will activate Heroic Strength, gaining a shield at a set amount, increasing its damage, and locking on to 1 Phantom Thief. On the next turn, it unleashes <color=#72C5FF>Gae Bolg</color> on that Phantom Thief, dealing heavy damage and inflicting an insta-kill effect.
If Cu Chulainn's <color=#FF423F>shield is broken</color>, it loses Heroic Strength and the lock on is canceled.

name: Yamata-no-Orochi
desc: A giant snake with eight heads that Susano-o defeated to save Kushinada-hime. The legendary sword Ame-no-Murakumo-no-Tsurugi, also known as the "Sword of Kusanagi," emerged from its belly.
strategy:
1. When Yamata-no-Orochi's HP reaches 0, it revives with new affinities and skills. It can revive up to 4 times.
2. After reviving 4 times, Yamata-no-Orochi will begin preparing and summon a Serpent's Tail.
3. When a Serpent's Tail is defeated, all Phantom Thieves gain <color=#FF423F>Ame-no-Murakumo</color>, which greatly increases the damage of their next attack.
4. When Yamata-no-Orochi is defeated, 4 Shadows appear.

name: Arahabaki
desc: A mysterious god of ancient Japan. Most famously worshipped by Nagasunehiko, who was defeated in battle against Emperor Jinmu, Arahabaki came to be treated as a symbol of rebellion and defiance.
strategy:
When Arahabaki takes damage from a skill, Resonance, or Highlight, it will record the attribute of the damage taken. (If damage from multiple attribute types is taken in the same turn, an attribute is recorded at random).
When Arahabaki takes damage of the <color=#FF423F>same attribute</color> it previously recorded, its <color=#FF423F>damage taken increases</color>. This effect can stack. When Arahabaki takes damage of a different attribute than the one it recorded, the increased damage taken effect is removed, and Arahabaki's damage increases.

name: Take-Minakata
desc: A Japanese god of war, hunting and fertility. He fought Take-Mikazuchi for control of Japan and lost. He escaped to Suwa, but has been prohibited to leave since then.
strategy:
When Take-Minakata takes damage from a skill, Resonance, or Highlight, it will record the attribute of the damage taken. (If damage from multiple attribute types is taken in the same turn, an attribute is recorded at random).
When Take-Minakata takes damage of a <color=#FF423F>different attribute</color> than what it previously recorded, its <color=#FF423F>damage taken increases</color>. This effect can stack. When Take-Minakata takes damage of the same attribute as the one it recorded, the increased damage taken effect is removed, and Take-Minakata's damage increases.

name: Kohryu
desc: Known as the Gold Dragon, it reigns over the Ssu-Ling, celestial creatures of Chinese lore. It is located at the center of the four beasts.
strategy:
Weaknesses and resistances are different than normal.
During battle, Kohryu will summon Seiryu, Byakko, Suzaku, and Genbu. When a Shadow is summoned, its corresponding Might is granted to all Shadows on the field. When a Shadow is defeated, the Shadows lose that Might and it is granted to all Phantom Thieves instead.
Seiryu's Might: Grants a shield equal to 10% of max HP every turn.
Byakko's Might: Increases Attack by 20%.
Suzaku's Might: Increases damage dealt by 20%.
Genbu's Might: Increases Defense by 20%.

name: Genbu
desc: One of the Ssu-Ling, celestial creatures in Chinese myth. It represents the direction north, the season of winter, and the element of water. Known to be a great warrior, it supports the Earth from below.

name: Suzaku
desc: One of the Ssu-Ling, celestial creatures in Chinese myth. It is a giant bird that is said to chirp in five beautiful voices. It represents the direction south, the season of summer, and the element of fire.

name: Byakko
desc: One of the Ssu-Ling, celestial creatures in Chinese myth. It represents the direction west, the season of autumn, and the element of metal. He is believed to be the king of all beasts.

name: Seiryu
desc: The noblest of the Ssu-Ling creatures of Chinese myth. It represents the direction east, the season of spring, and the element of wood. It dwells in a palace at the bottom of the ocean.

name: Clotho
desc: The youngest of the three Moirae Sisters of Greek legend. She spins the threads of life with her spindle.
strategy: Clotho uses Moirai Binding to grant a random Phantom Thief the Thread of Fate.

name: Lachesis
desc: The middle sister of the three Moirae Sisters of Greek legend. She is the apportioner, measuring the thread which determines each person's lifespan.
strategy: Lachesis uses Moirai Spinning to change a Phantom Thief's Thread of Fate to <color=#72C5FF>Weave of Fate</color>.

name: Atropos
desc: The eldest of the three Moirae Sisters of Greek mythology. She cuts the threads of life for those whose time has come.
strategy:
At certain times, Atropos will use <color=#72C5FF>Moirai Cutting</color>, dealing severe damage to Phantom Thieves with the Weave of Fate.
1. After Atropos has acted 10 times.
2. After Clotho or Lachesis have been defeated.
3. After Atropos has been defeated.

strategy: <color=#FF423F>Generates additional buff effects</color> for Phantom Thieves with Threads of Fate when defeated.

name: Hecatoncheires
desc: Giants born from Uranus and Gaia. The name means "those with a hundred arms." During the war of the Titans, Zeus freed them from the Underworld to help him obtain victory.
strategy:
Shadows have different weaknesses and resistances than normal.
1. At the start of the battle, Hecatoncheires has 100 <color=#72C5FF>Arms of Protection</color> stacks and reduces its damage taken based on the number of stacks. While it has Arms of Protection, it also reduces its final damage taken by 70% through <color=#72C5FF>Arms of Defense</color>.
2. Hecatoncheires will summon Slime and Black Ooze. When Slime is defeated, 2 <color=#72C5FF>Arms of Protection</color> stacks are removed. When Black Ooze is defeated, 10 <color=#72C5FF>Arms of Protection</color> stacks are removed. For each <color=#72C5FF>Arms of Protection</color> stack removed, all Phantom Thieves gain <color=#72C5FF>Arms of Strength</color>. Arms of Strength: Increases damage based on the number of stacks.
3. When Hecatoncheires has 80 or more <color=#72C5FF>Arms of Protection</color> stacks, it becomes invincible and will not attack. It keeps 4 Slimes on the field, and gains 1 <color=#72C5FF>Arms of Might</color> stack every turn. Arms of Might: Increases damage based on the number of stacks.
4. When Hecatoncheires has less than 80 <color=#72C5FF>Arms of Protection</color> stacks, it loses its invincibility, and begins to attack and summon 2 Black Oozes every turn. When it takes damage, 2 <color=#72C5FF>Arms of Protection</color> stacks are removed.
5. When <color=#72C5FF>Arms of Protection</color> reaches 0 stacks, Hecatoncheires enters the Last Stand state. Last Stand: Greatly increases final damage and changes the attack pattern.

name: Wraith of Envy
strategy:
Wraith of Envy:
1. The Wraith of Envy and its eyes share a <color=#72C5FF>Soul Link</color>.
Soul Link: Distributes all damage received between all Shadows who share this condition, based on the percentage of their current HP.
2. Each turn, the Wraith of Envy will lock on to 1 Phantom Thief, and deal heavy damage to that Phantom Thief on the next turn.

name: Wraith of Envy
strategy:
Wraith of Envy:
1. While both of the Wraith of Envy's eyes are present, all affinities will be Resist. When both eyes have been defeated, it enters a Weakened state and will take more damage.
2. When the Wraith of Envy's eyes are defeated, they will revive after 3 turns.
3. The Wraith of Envy will gather power every other turn, and on the next turn uses Dark Whisper, dealing heavy Curse damage to all Phantom Thieves. If both eyes are defeated while gathering power, Dark Whisper will not be activated. If one eye is defeated while gathering power, the damage of Dark Whisper will be decreased by 30%.

name: Wraith of Envy
strategy:
Wraith of Envy:
1. The Wraith of Envy and its eyes are in the <color=#72C5FF>Soul Link</color> state.
Soul Link: Distributes all damage received between all Shadows who share this condition, based on the percentage of their current HP.
2. The Wraith of Envy is Enraged, and its damage increases every turn.

name: Ara Mitama
desc: One of the four aspects of Shinto thought, it has the power to grant ferocity. It is said to aid in one's bravery, growth, and endeavors, though it can lead in a negative direction.

name: Asura
desc: The Hindu king of Asuras is named Maha Vairocana, or "One Who Shines On All." In Buddhism, he is known as Dainichi Nyorai.
strategy:
Asura has no weaknesses or resistances.
1. Jikokuten has <color=#72C5FF>Blade of Sanctuary</color>.
Blade of Sanctuary: Grants a shield to all Shadows. Lasts for 2 turns.
2. Zouchouten has <color=#72C5FF>Growth of All Things</color>.
Growth of All Things: Permanently increases damage for all Shadows.
3. Koumokuten has <color=#72C5FF>Eye of Heaven</color>.
Eye of Heaven: Selects 1 Phantom Thief. Increases their damage taken, and has Shadows focus attacks on them next turn.
4. Bishamonten has <color=#72C5FF>Parasol of Chaos</color>.
Parasol of Chaos: Covers the Shadow with the lowest HP, and changes all affinities to Drain for 2 turns.
5. When the number of Shadows falls below 3, they will sacrifice themselves to summon <color=#72C5FF>Asura</color>. <color=#72C5FF>Asura</color> has the special skills of the sacrificed Shadows (if there are less than 2 special skills, it will gain another Shadow's special skill at random). <color=#72C5FF>Asura</color> activates its skill every turn.

name: Trumpeter
desc: Angels that sound the trumpets at the time of the apocalypse. As each trumpet sounds, the more plagues and disasters will occur, turning the earth into a land of death and suffering.
strategy:
These Shadows have no weaknesses or resistances.
1. At the start of battle, Trumpeter summons 4 Shadows, and becomes invincible. These Shadows share a <color=#72C5FF>Soul Link</color>, and if all four are defeated, Trumpeter will enter its Dire state.
Soul Link: Distributes all damage received between all Shadows who share this condition, based on the percentage of their current HP.
2. Trumpeter and the Shadows will sound their horns once every 3 turns. They cannot sound their horns if they are affected by a spiritual ailment.
3. White Rider: On Trumpeter's command, it will sound the <color=#72C5FF>Horn of Pestilence</color>, decreasing the max HP of 1 random Phantom Thief.
4. Red Rider: On Trumpeter's command, it will sound the <color=#72C5FF>Horn of War</color>, granting itself the <color=#72C5FF>Horn of War</color> status. When this status is active, it will counterattack when attacked. Lasts for 1 turn.
5. Black Rider: On Trumpeter's command, it will sound the <color=#72C5FF>Horn of Famine</color>, increasing the SP cost of skills for 1 random Phantom Thief.
6. Pale Rider: On Trumpeter's command, it will sound the <color=#72C5FF>Horn of Death</color>, decreasing the healing effect of all Phantom Thieves' skills, and increasing all Shadows' damage. Lasts for 2 turns.
7. Trumpeter: Each time a Shadow sounds a horn, Trumpeter gains 1 <color=#72C5FF>Power of Ruin</color> stack. After all the Shadows have been commanded, Trumpeter will prepare for 1 turn before sounding the <color=#72C5FF>Horn of Ruin</color>. This will spend all <color=#72C5FF>Power of Ruin</color> stacks to deal Almighty damage to all Phantom Thieves (deals higher damage based on the Attack of all Shadows). Additional effects are based on the number of <color=#72C5FF>Power of Ruin</color> stacks.
1 stack: Final attack power increases by 25%.
2 stacks: Damage increases by 15%.
3 stacks: All Shadows heal 10% of their HP.
4 stacks: This attack is guaranteed to be a critical hit.
8. After all Shadows have been defeated once, Trumpeter will enter its Dire state, sacrificing 50% of its own HP to revive the Shadows, and becoming invincible again. The Shadows share a <color=#72C5FF>Soul Link</color>, and once they are defeated, Trumpeter will lose its invincibility.
9. When in its Dire state, Trumpeter does not spend <color=#72C5FF>Power of Ruin</color> when it sounds the <color=#72C5FF>Horn of Ruin</color>, but still gains additional effects based on the number of <color=#72C5FF>Power of Ruin</color> stacks. The number of stacks of <color=#72C5FF>Power of Ruin</color> will increase the damage of all Shadows by a set amount.

name: Seth
desc: The Egyptian god of the desert, chaos, and evil. He murdered his brother, Osiris, and tried to become chief god, but he was castrated by Osiris's son, Horus.
strategy:
Shadows have different weaknesses and resistances than normal.
1. Seth controls day and night, and switches the status of Dazzling Daylight and Obscuring Darkness each turn.
2. When at the verge of death, Seth will defeat all Shadows present and change to Dire Seth. When it does, if Horus is present, it will change to always Dazzling Daylight state and summon Isis and Horus. If Horus is not present, it will change to always Obscuring Darkness state and summon Thoth and Anubis.

name: Isis
desc: Osiris's wife as well as his younger sister. Upon the death of her husband, she revived him with her incredible magic power. Isis is seen at many gravesites as the guardian goddess of the dead.
strategy:
Shadows have different weaknesses and resistances than normal.
1. While Dazzling Daylight is active, the final damage Isis deals is increased by 25%, and its final damage taken is decreased by 25%. While Obscuring Darkness is active, final damage dealt is decreased by 25%, and final damage taken is increased by 25%.
2. While Dazzling Daylight is active, Isis uses Diarama, healing the Shadow with the lowest HP percentage. Each turn, Amulet of Rebirth is granted to Seth. At 4 Amulet of Rebirth stacks, they are exchanged for 1 Power of Rebirth stack. When a Shadow with Power of Rebirth is at low HP, it spends 1 Power of Rebirth to restore 25% of its max HP.

name: Horus
desc: An ancient god of Egypt whose eyes are the sun and moon. Revered by some as the chief god, he is often depicted as a hawk or a falcon.
strategy:
Shadows have different weaknesses and resistances than normal.
1. While Dazzling Daylight is active, the final damage Horus deals is increased by 25%, and its final damage taken is decreased by 25%. While Obscuring Darkness is active, final damage dealt is decreased by 25%, and final damage taken is increased by 25%.
2. While Dazzling Daylight is active, Horus grants Sun God's Blessing to Seth every turn. At 4 Sun God's Blessing stacks, they are exchanged for 1 Sun God's Power stack. When a Shadow has Sun God's Power, its final damage dealt is increased by 20%.

name: Thoth
desc: Egyptian moon god that takes the form of a baboon, he is the one who measures time. He gave Isis the power to resurrect Osiris after he was killed by the evil god Seth.
strategy:
Shadows have different weaknesses and resistances than normal.
1. While Dazzling Daylight is active, the final damage that Thoth deals is decreased by 25%, and its final damage taken is increased by 25%. While Obscuring Darkness is active, final damage dealt is increased by 25%, and final damage taken is decreased by 25%. 
2. While Obscuring Darkness is active, Thoth alternates between using Wisdom Theurgy and Shield Theurgy.
Wisdom Theurgy: Select the Shadow with the lowest HP and change all of that target's affinities to Resist for 2 turns.
Shield Theurgy: Grant a shield to all allies for 2 turns.

name: Anubis
desc: The jackal-headed god of the dead and embalming from Egyptian myth. He weighs the hearts of the dead to determine their final destination.
strategy:
Shadows have different weaknesses and resistances than normal.
1. While Dazzling Daylight is active, the final damage that Anubis deals is decreased by 25%, and its final damage taken is increased by 25%. While Obscuring Darkness is active, final damage dealt is increased by 25%, and final damage taken is decreased by 25%.
2. While Obscuring Darkness is active, Anubis inflicts Curse of Annihilation on 1 random Phantom Thief each turn, after which it inflicts it on the Phantom Thief with the most Curse of Annihilation stacks. Curse of Annihilation insta-kills when it reaches 4 stacks and can be prioritized for removal.
3. When Anubis is defeated, it deals Curse damage to all Phantom Thieves.

name: Dire Seth
desc: The Egyptian god of the desert, chaos, and evil. He murdered his brother, Osiris, and tried to become chief god, but he was castrated by Osiris's son, Horus.
strategy:
Shadows have different weaknesses and resistances than normal.
1. Seth controls day and night, and switches the status of Dazzling Daylight and Obscuring Darkness each turn.
2. When at the verge of death, Seth will defeat all Shadows present and change to Dire Seth. When it does, if Horus is present, it will change to always Dazzling Daylight state and summon Isis and Horus. If Horus is not present, it will change to always Obscuring Darkness state and summon Thoth and Anubis.

name: Isis
desc: Osiris's wife as well as his younger sister. Upon the death of her husband, she revived him with her incredible magic power. Isis is seen at many gravesites as the guardian goddess of the dead.
strategy:
Shadows have different weaknesses and resistances than normal.
1. While Dazzling Daylight is active, the final damage Isis deals is increased by 25%, and its final damage taken is decreased by 25%. While Obscuring Darkness is active, final damage dealt is decreased by 25%, and final damage taken is increased by 25%.
2. While Dazzling Daylight is active, Isis uses Diarama, healing the Shadow with the lowest HP percentage. Each turn, Amulet of Rebirth is granted to Seth. At 4 Amulet of Rebirth stacks, they are exchanged for 1 Power of Rebirth stack. When a Shadow with Power of Rebirth is at low HP, it spends 1 Power of Rebirth to restore 25% of its max HP.

name: Horus
desc: An ancient god of Egypt whose eyes are the sun and moon. Revered by some as the chief god, he is often depicted as a hawk or a falcon.
strategy:
Shadows have different weaknesses and resistances than normal.
1. While Dazzling Daylight is active, the final damage Horus deals is increased by 25%, and its final damage taken is decreased by 25%. While Obscuring Darkness is active, final damage dealt is decreased by 25%, and final damage taken is increased by 25%.
2. While Dazzling Daylight is active, Horus grants Sun God's Blessing to Seth every turn. At 4 Sun God's Blessing stacks, they are exchanged for 1 Sun God's Power stack. When a Shadow has Sun God's Power, its final damage dealt is increased by 20%.

name: Thoth
desc: Egyptian moon god that takes the form of a baboon, he is the one who measures time. He gave Isis the power to resurrect Osiris after he was killed by the evil god Seth.
strategy:
Shadows have different weaknesses and resistances than normal.
1. While Dazzling Daylight is active, the final damage that Thoth deals is decreased by 25%, and its final damage taken is increased by 25%. While Obscuring Darkness is active, final damage dealt is increased by 25%, and final damage taken is decreased by 25%. 
2. While Obscuring Darkness is active, Thoth alternates between using Wisdom Theurgy and Shield Theurgy.
Wisdom Theurgy: Select the Shadow with the lowest HP and change all of that target's affinities to Resist for 2 turns.
Shield Theurgy: Grant a shield to all allies for 2 turns.

name: Anubis
desc: The jackal-headed god of the dead and embalming from Egyptian myth. He weighs the hearts of the dead to determine their final destination.
strategy:
Shadows have different weaknesses and resistances than normal.
1. While Dazzling Daylight is active, the final damage that Anubis deals is decreased by 25%, and its final damage taken is increased by 25%. While Obscuring Darkness is active, final damage dealt is increased by 25%, and final damage taken is decreased by 25%.
2. While Obscuring Darkness is active, Anubis inflicts Curse of Annihilation on 1 random Phantom Thief each turn, after which it inflicts it on the Phantom Thief with the most Curse of Annihilation stacks. Curse of Annihilation insta-kills when it reaches 4 stacks and can be prioritized for removal.
3. When Anubis is defeated, it deals Curse damage to all Phantom Thieves.

desc: A dog spirit said to possess people in Japanese lore. Those possessed are in a state of "inu-tsuki" and lose consciousness. Onmyoji use Inugami as familiars.

name: Moha
desc: An unknown person's Shadow. It gazes down on the ignorant with contempt.
strategy:
1. When Moha's HP reaches 0 and it becomes Wrathful Moha, it gains 8 Wrath stacks.
2. After acting each turn, if Wrathful Moha has taken damage during that turn, its Wrath increases by 4. If it has not taken damage during the turn, its Wrath decreases by 1.
3. If Wrathful Moha has 12 Wrath stacks at the end of its turn, it will spend all Wrath to activate Rapid Ascent, and on the next turn, use Sphinxian Dive to deal heavy Physical damage to all Phantom Thieves.
4. When Wrathful Moha is in battle, the Phantom Thieves gain a small amount of Ballista Energy at the end of each turn.
5. When the Phantom Thieves deal weakness damage to Wrathful Moha, they gain a large amount of Ballista Energy. This can only be activated once per turn.
6. When the Phantom Thieves have 100 Ballista Energy at the start of their turn, they will spend 100 Ballista Energy to attack Wrathful Moha with a Ballista Shot, putting it in a Weakened state and causing it to lose all Wrath.

strategy: Corporobo MDL-GM uses skills to buff and heal Shadows.

name: Corporobo MDL-ED
desc: A corporobo that protects Avidya. It will never defy the orders of Avidya.
strategy: Corporobo MDL-ED will use Team-Building Exercise to drain all other Shadows' HP to strengthen itself.

name: Avidya
desc: An unknown person's Shadow. It despises the ignorant and the indifferent, possessing a twisted fixation on offering salvation.
strategy:
1. Avidya cannot be targeted in the first phase of battle, and will continuously summon Corporobos to fight. After a certain number of Corporobos have been defeated, Avidya will move to the second phase.
2. Avidya cannot be targeted in the second phase of battle, and will summon a team of powerful Corporobos to fight. When all of the Corporobos have been defeated, Avidya will move to the third phase, where he can be targeted and will not use any skills.
3. During the battle, Avidya will use <color=#72C5FF>Sacrifice Order</color> on randomly selected Corporobos, who will self-destruct after 2 turns, dealing heavy damage to the Phantom Thieves.
